<div class=3D"innerCell">=20
<p>Learn how to start creating and using a Landing page for your business. =
This section provides essential information to start working with layout, z=
ones and blocks within the Landing Page.</p>
<h1 id=3D"Creatinglayouts,zonesandblocks-Landingpage">Landing page</h1>
<p>A Landing Page is a page designed to be the visitor's entry point into y=
our website.</p>
<h2 id=3D"Creatinglayouts,zonesandblocks-UnderstandtheessentialconceptsofeZ=
LandingPage">Understand the essential concepts of eZ Landing Page</h2>
<p>A <a href=3D"https://doc.ez.no/display/MAIN/Glossary#Glossary-LandingPag=
e" rel=3D"nofollow">Landing Page</a> has a customizable&nbsp;<span class=3D=
"DEF"><span class=3D"DEF"><a href=3D"https://doc.ez.no/display/MAIN/Glossar=
y#Glossary-Layout" rel=3D"nofollow">layout</a></span></span> with multiple =
<a href=3D"https://doc.ez.no/display/MAIN/Glossary#Glossary-Zone" rel=3D"no=
follow">zones</a> where you can place predefined&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://do=
c.ez.no/display/MAIN/Glossary#Glossary-Block" rel=3D"nofollow">blocks</a> w=
ith content on <a href=3D"https://doc.ez.no/display/MAIN/Glossary#Glossary-=
Dynamicpage" rel=3D"nofollow">Dynamic</a> page. It can be, for example, an =
article, a photo gallery or a blog post.&nbsp;</p>
<p>Technically, these are special types of Content items (aka objects). Eac=
h single Content item is an instance of a&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://doc.ez.no=
/display/MAIN/Glossary#Glossary-ContentType" rel=3D"nofollow">Content Type<=
/a> (a "template"/"blueprint"). This template or blueprint for <a href=3D"h=
ttps://doc.ez.no/display/MAIN/Glossary#Glossary-Content" rel=3D"nofollow">C=
ontent</a> defines <a href=3D"https://doc.ez.no/display/MAIN/Glossary#Gloss=
ary-Field" rel=3D"nofollow">Fields </a>and their <a href=3D"https://doc.ez.=
no/display/MAIN/Glossary#Glossary-FieldType" rel=3D"nofollow">Field Types</=
a>. Then they are assigned <a href=3D"https://doc.ez.no/display/MAIN/Glossa=
ry#Glossary-FieldValue" rel=3D"nofollow">Field Values</a> when a Content it=
em is created based on this Content Type. Content Type is conceptually simi=
lar to a class in object-oriented programming.</p>
<p>In addition to having blocks represent content items, they can also repr=
esent any type of content. You can add any number of parameters as input to=
 a block and use this to e.g. display a Youtube video, an RSS feed, externa=
l banner advertisement or a Javascript game if you like. You can build a se=
t of re-usable widgets that the editorial team can freely place on Landing =
Pages, giving the flexibility and power to quickly build engaging Landing P=
ages without involvement of IT, once the blocks are created.</p>
</div>=20
</div>=20
